## RTOS Abstraction (`rtos.c`)

`rtos_initialize(uint flags)` is the single entry point for all OS primitive setup:
mutexes, threads, semaphores, timers. `flags` is a bitmask — only requested subsystems
are initialized. Status variables are pessimistically pre-set to `RTOS_ERROR` and only
overwritten on explicit success.

`rtos_terminate()` mirrors `rtos_initialize()` exactly — every primitive initialized must
be torn down.

