## Build System

The build pipeline is a stateful Bash chain:

```
build_app
  └── build_app_unfiltered
        └── build_mod          ← discovers .c/.cpp/.fc/.vml sources per module
              └── makefile_mod ← invokes GNU Make for compilation and .a / ELF linking
```

Key behaviors:
- Any `$?` != 0 sets `build_result = -1` and skips linking (prevents malformed artifacts)
- Override with `--force_link` only in emergencies — never for delivery builds
- Exported uppercase environment variables carry configuration to Make
- Output is routed through `egrep` to surface only warnings and errors
- Source file types: `.c`, `.cpp` (flight logic), `.fc` (table configs), `.vml` (Virtual
  Machine Language — compiled separately, linked into final binary)

