## Known Channel / Port Mapping (ORTHUS / Brick Mk4)

This mapping was hardware-verified on the ORTHUS dev machine with Brick Mk4 + CMV4000.
It resolves HSI-001 (pre-CDR HSI item).

| Layer | Identifier | Maps to | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| STAR-API channel index | 0 | SDK config service | Reserved — do not use for data |
| STAR-API channel index | 1 OUT (`tmCmdTxChannel`) | Router FIFO port 5 | TC commands (0x20) routed out port 2 to camera |
| STAR-API channel index | 1 IN  (`tmCmdRxChannel`) | Router FIFO port 5 | TM replies (0x21) received back |
| STAR-API channel index | 2 IN  (`videoRxChannel`) | Router FIFO port 6 | Video frames (0x22) inbound |
| Physical enclosure "Port 1" | — | Router port 2 | One-based; offset by internal config port 0 |

**Opening channel index 1 OUT and channel index 1 IN simultaneously is safe** — the SDK
returns independent `STAR_CHANNEL_ID` handles for TX and RX directions. This is confirmed
supported by SDK v6.01 in single-threaded use.

**`(STAR_CHANNEL_ID)0` is the SDK invalid/unset handle sentinel** (equivalent to `NULL`).
It is NOT "channel index 0" (the config service). These are completely different types:
- Channel index → `U8` argument passed into `STAR_openChannelToLocalDevice()`
- `STAR_CHANNEL_ID` → opaque handle returned by that call

Always initialize `STAR_CHANNEL_ID` fields to `(STAR_CHANNEL_ID)0` and check before use.

